The paper deals with the problem of question routing in a community-based question and answering platform, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and social networks (cs.SOC). The authors also mention the use of network representation learning models, which is a popular technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) and complex networks (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of textual data, which is relevant to the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR) and social networks (cs.SI).
